{
  "texts": [
    "Under the all-in-one schema, taking the UCR dataset as an example, we mix all samples together from all time series' training sets during the training phase.",
    "Under zero-shot schema, we use a fixed random seed to split UCR into two subsets, each of which includes half of the time series.",
    "We mix all training samples from one subset, and the other acts as the test set.",
    "All methods share the same training set in zero-shot mode.",
    "D. Evaluation MetricsFollowing the event-based evaluation criterion outlined in Sec."
  ]
}